705439f.title: Brooklyn: Liberty Avenue - Essex Street
705439f.text:
Liberty Ave., north side, east of Essex Street, showing a small frame
house, once a blacksmith shop and home of John Likewise. He established
his wheelwright shop here in 1863. It was still occupied in 1902. (In
the rear is a 4-story factory).
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
